## SKOS displays w/ SPARQL

June 4, 2008   
[rdf](https://inkdroid.org/2008/06/04/skos-displays-w-sparql/tag/rdf) [skos](https://inkdroid.org/2008/06/04/skos-displays-w-sparql/tag/skos) [sparql](https://inkdroid.org/2008/06/04/skos-displays-w-sparql/tag/sparql) 

---

I’m just in the process of getting my head around[SPARQL](http://www.w3.org/TR/rdf-sparql-query/) a bit more. At $work, Clay and I ran up against a situation where we wanted a query that would return a subgraph from an entire SKOS concept scheme for any assertions involving a particular concept URI as the subject. Easy enough right?

  DESCRIBE <http://lcsh.info/sh96010624#concept>

The thing is, for human readable displays we don’t want to display the URIs for related concepts (skos:broader, skos:narrower or skos:related) … we want to display the nice skos:prefLabel for them. Something akin to:

![](http://inkdroid.org/images/ethnoscience.png) 

So how can we get a subgraph for a concept as well as any concept that might be directly related to it, in a single query? We came up with the following but I’d be interested in more elegant solutions:

PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>

CONSTRUCT {<http://lcsh.info/sh96010624#concept> ?p1 ?o1. ?s2 ?p2 ?o2}
WHERE
{
    {<http://lcsh.info/sh96010624#concept> ?p1 ?o1.}
    UNION 
    {
        {<http://lcsh.info/sh96010624#concept> skos:narrower ?s2.}
        {?s2 ?p2 ?o2.}
    }
    UNION
    { 
        {<http://lcsh.info/sh96010624#concept> skos:broader ?s2.}
        {?s2 ?p2 ?o2.}
    }
    UNION
    { 
        {<http://lcsh.info/sh96010624#concept> skos:related ?s2.}
        {?s2 ?p2 ?o2.}
    }           
}

The above ran quite nicely in my[Arc](http://arc.semsol.org/) playground. Any suggestions or ideas on how to boil this down would be appreciated. I also wanted to jot this query in the likely event that I forget how I did it.

